---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Property Encryption
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- config server uses a public repository for sensitive data
- config server is supporting encryption and decryption of property values

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
prefix
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
encrypt/decrypt endpoints
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Encrypted values are prefixed with the string {cipher} and can be generated by an
REST-call to the path ‘/encrypt', if the server is configured to use a
symmetric key or a key pair

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
yaml vs properties
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
yaml: must surround encrypted and prefixed values with single-quotes

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
symmetric cryptography
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- set the property encrypt.key in  application.properties to a random secret
or
- pass-in the environment variable ENCRYPT_KEY

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
asymmetric cryptography
---------------------------------------------------------------------------------
- set ‘encrypt.key' to a PEM-encoded string value
or
- configure a keystore to use